	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-24T04:11:16">Synthomer Plc is a United Kingdom-based specialty chemical Company. The Company is a producer of aqueous polymers. Its products include Synthetic latex, which consists of three principal product families, such as Styrene Butadiene Rubber (SBR), Nitrile Butadiene Rubber (NBR) and High Solids Styrene Butadiene Rubber; Dispersions (HSSBR), which consists of primarily Vinyl and Acrylic-based emulsion polymers used in a range of applications, including in the coating, construction, adhesives and textile industries; Compounds, which includes products that are formulated using SBR latex, HSSBR latex, Natural Rubber latex and a range of other functional materials, and Specialties, which consist of a number of specialty polymers, mainly non-aqueous, including Polyvinyl Alcohol, Liquid Polybutadiene, HSSBR latex and Chloroprene. It caters to markets, such as Health and Protection, Paper, Construction and Coatings, Carpet Compounds and Foam, Functional Polymers and Performance Polymers.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-29T11:32:49">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Synthomer PLC revenues decreased 8% to L468.7M. Net income increased 23% to L29.2M. Revenues reflect Europe &amp; North America segment decrease of 15% to L307M. Net income reflects Asia &amp; Rest of World segment income increase from L4.5M to L16.1M. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.03. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items increased from L0.07 to L0.09.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
